59.3	Single_point_of_failure	Single point of failure	A single point of failure is a part of a system that, if it fails, will stop the entire system from working. They are undesirable in any system with a goal of high availability or reliability, be it a business practice, software application, or other industrial system.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Single_Point_of_Failure.png/200px-Single_Point_of_Failure.png
